-- Everton Captain Phil Neville Will Leave Club at End of Season
-- B y   D a n i e l l e   R o s s i n g h
-- 2013-04-09T09:01:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-09/everton-captain-phil-neville-will-leave-club-at-end-of-season.html
Everton defender and captain  Phil
Neville  will leave the club this summer after eight years.  “I want to continue to play at the top level as long as I
physically can, and will be weighing up my options before making
a decision on my next move,” Neville, 36, said in a statement
on the club website today.  Neville, who joined Everton from Manchester United in 2005,
is a member of the coaching staff of  England ’s Under-21 team. He
scored eight goals in 303 appearances for Everton.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Danielle Rossingh in London at 
